WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:06.000
Priya: Thanks for joining this call Amit. I wanted to understand how you currently handle customer feedback.

2
00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:22.000
Amit: Sure. So right now we have a Slack channel where the support team drops customer complaints. I try to read it every morning but honestly I miss half of them.

3
00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Priya: And when you are deciding what to build next, where do you go for that information?

4
00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:58.000
Amit: Mostly my memory. I remember the loudest complaints. But last month we built a dashboard feature because one enterprise client kept asking for it. Turned out nobody else wanted it. We wasted three weeks of engineering time.

5
00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:15.000
Priya: That must have been frustrating. How did the engineering team react?

6
00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:40.000
Amit: They were angry. Our lead engineer told me he needs proof before he builds anything now. He said show me the data, show me the customer quotes, stop coming to me with gut feelings. And honestly he is right.

7
00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:55.000
Priya: So the trust between product and engineering broke down?

8
00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:20.000
Amit: Completely. Now every sprint planning feels like a courtroom. I am the lawyer trying to convince the jury. But I have no evidence. Just my memory of what customers said two weeks ago on a Zoom call.

9
00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:35.000
Priya: Have you tried recording those Zoom calls?

10
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:55.000
Amit: We do record them but nobody watches a 45 minute recording. We tried Otter for transcription but it just gives you a wall of text. Finding the one quote I need takes longer than the original call.

11
00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:10.000
Priya: What would the ideal solution look like for you?

12
00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:35.000
Amit: I want to upload a Zoom call and get back a list of pain points with the exact customer quote attached. Not a summary. The actual words they said. So when my engineer asks why are we building this, I can click a link and play the exact 30 seconds where the customer described the problem.
